---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="MSME Loan - Govt Schemes for Micro, Small & Medium Enterprises | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>MSME Loan</span>
      </div>
      <h1>MSME Loan</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Access affordable loans for micro, small, and medium enterprises through government-backed schemes like MUDRA, CGTMSE, and Stand-Up India. Interest rates from 8.50% p.a. with collateral-free options up to ₹2 crore.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-indian-rupee-sign"></i>
          <span>Loan Amount: ₹50K - ₹2 Cr</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Interest: 8.50% onwards</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-shield-halved"></i>
          <span>Govt-Backed Guarantee</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>What is an MSME Loan?</h2>
          <p>MSME loans are specially designed financial products for Micro, Small, and Medium Enterprises that form the backbone of India's economy. These loans are available through banks, NBFCs, and government-backed schemes like Pradhan Mantri MUDRA Yojana (PMMY), Credit Guarantee Fund Trust for MSEs (CGTMSE), and Stand-Up India. MSMEs registered under the Udyam portal can access collateral-free loans at subsidized interest rates with government credit guarantees.</p>
          <p>At TrueCred Loan Expert, we help MSME owners navigate the complex landscape of government and private lending. Whether you are a micro enterprise needing ₹50,000 for inventory or a medium enterprise seeking ₹2 crore for expansion, we match you with the best scheme and lender. Our platform provides end-to-end support — from Udyam registration and scheme eligibility check to application filing and document preparation. Over 5,000 MSMEs have received funding through our platform in 2025-26.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">8.50%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Lowest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">₹2 Crore</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Loan (CGTMSE)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">Zero</span>
              <span class="info-label">Collateral Required</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>MSME Loan Interest Rates — April 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Processing Fee</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>SBI (MUDRA)</td>
                <td>8.50% onwards</td>
                <td>Nil</td>
                <td>7 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Bank of Baroda</td>
                <td>9.25% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>7 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Union Bank (CGTMSE)</td>
                <td>9.50% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 1.00%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>HDFC Bank</td>
                <td>11.50% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 2.00%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>SIDBI</td>
                <td>9.75% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 0.50%</td>
                <td>10 Years</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Registered MSME with valid Udyam registration certificate</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Business vintage of at least 1 year (6 months for MUDRA Shishu)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Annual turnover within MSME limits — Micro: up to ₹5 Cr, Small: up to ₹50 Cr, Medium: up to ₹250 Cr</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> GST registration (if applicable based on turnover threshold)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> No NPA or default with any bank in the last 12 months</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Business owner aged between 21 and 65 years with clean credit history</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Apply for an MSME Loan</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Get Udyam Registration</h4>
              <p>Register your business on the Udyam portal (free) to get an MSME certificate, which is mandatory for government scheme benefits.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Choose the Right Scheme</h4>
              <p>Based on your loan amount and business stage — MUDRA (up to ₹10L), CGTMSE (up to ₹2Cr), or regular MSME loans from banks.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Prepare Documents</h4>
              <p>Gather Udyam certificate, business financials, GST returns, and bank statements. TrueCred guides you on scheme-specific requirements.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Apply & Track</h4>
              <p>Submit your application through TrueCred. We work with banking partners to expedite processing and disbursal within 7-15 days.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Udyam Registration Certificate (MSME certificate)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Business PAN card and GST registration certificate</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Last 2 years ITR with audited balance sheet and P&L statement</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Last 12 months bank statements of the primary business account</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> KYC of proprietor/partners/directors — Aadhaar, PAN, photograph</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Business address proof — rent agreement, utility bill, or property documents</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i> Apply for MSME Loan</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Loan Amount</option>
                  <option value="50000">₹50,000</option>
                  <option value="100000">₹1,00,000</option>
                  <option value="500000">₹5,00,000</option>
                  <option value="1000000">₹10,00,000</option>
                  <option value="2500000">₹25,00,000</option>
                  <option value="5000000">₹50,00,000</option>
                  <option value="10000000">₹1,00,00,000</option>
                  <option value="20000000">₹2,00,00,000</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="City" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/loan-against-property"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Loan Against Property</a>
              <a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Gold Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/car-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Car Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Score</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
              <a href="/pages/insurance"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Insurance</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Got Questions?</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Common questions about MSME loans and government schemes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What is the difference between MUDRA and CGTMSE loans?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              MUDRA loans are for micro and small enterprises needing up to ₹10 lakh in three categories: Shishu (up to ₹50,000), Kishore (₹50,000 to ₹5 lakh), and Tarun (₹5 lakh to ₹10 lakh). CGTMSE provides credit guarantee up to ₹2 crore for collateral-free loans to MSEs. MUDRA is primarily for smaller ticket sizes, while CGTMSE covers larger funding needs with government-backed guarantee.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Do I need collateral for an MSME loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Under CGTMSE scheme, loans up to ₹2 crore are available without collateral, backed by government guarantee. MUDRA loans up to ₹10 lakh are also collateral-free. For regular bank MSME loans above ₹2 crore, collateral in the form of property, FD, or business assets may be required. Many NBFCs also offer unsecured MSME loans up to ₹50 lakh based on business performance.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How long does MSME loan approval take?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              MUDRA loans through public sector banks take 7-15 business days. CGTMSE-backed loans take 10-20 days due to guarantee processing. NBFC and fintech MSME loans can be processed in 3-7 days. The timeline depends on document completeness, bank processing speed, and loan amount. TrueCred expedites the process through pre-verified applications and dedicated relationship managers.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can a startup apply for an MSME loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes, startups registered as MSMEs can apply for MUDRA Shishu loans (up to ₹50,000) with minimal documentation, even with less than 6 months of business history. For larger amounts, Stand-Up India scheme offers ₹10 lakh to ₹1 crore for SC/ST and women entrepreneurs. SIDBI's Fund of Funds also supports SEBI-registered startups through venture capital.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What are the interest subsidy schemes available for MSMEs?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Key subsidy schemes include: (a) Interest Subvention Scheme — 2% interest subsidy on fresh/incremental MSME loans, (b) CLCSS (Credit Linked Capital Subsidy) — 15% capital subsidy for technology upgradation, (c) State-level subsidies varying by region. Eligible MSMEs can effectively reduce their borrowing cost to 6-7% p.a. through these subsidies. TrueCred helps you identify and apply for all applicable schemes.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Get Your MSME Loan at Subsidized Rates</h3>
          <p>Access government-backed schemes with interest rates from 8.50% p.a. and zero collateral requirement.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline" style="color:#fff;border:2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5);padding:14px 32px;font-size:0.95rem;">
          Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
